Patient: What kind of food should I eat?
Healthcare Educator: You should eat more fruits, vegetables, whole grains, and lean proteins. Avoid processed foods.

Patient: Is it alright to eat fried chicken?
Healthcare Educator: It's better to have baked or grilled chicken. Fried foods can be high in unhealthy fats and salt. 

Patient: What about snacks? I love chips.
Healthcare Educator: Choose fresh fruits or nuts over chips. They are healthier and have less salt.

Patient: Can I put salt on my food?
Healthcare Educator: Try to limit your salt intake. Too much salt can make your heart work harder.

Patient: Is it okay to drink soda?
Healthcare Educator: Water is the best choice. Soda has lots of sugar which isn't good for your heart.